projects.description: "Towards effective strategies for mobile robot using Reinforcement Learning" article and project were prepared for "Black Sea Science 2023" International Scientific Competition, organized by Odesa National University of Technology. The project uses Reinforcement Learning and graph algorithms (like A*) for path planning and strategy development for mobile robots. The study compares their performance in terms of efficiency, scalability, and real-world applicability. Results indicate that RL algorithms have the potential to provide more effective and scalable solutions.
projects.title: Strategies for mobile robot path planning using Reinforcement Learning

projects.description:
Commercial project for Upwork client. Platform that automates the generation of comments for social media posts. This tool leverages the OpenAI API and Instagram API.

Features:
- OpenAI API Integration: The platform generates comments that are contextually relevant and engaging, saving users time and effort in crafting their own comments.
- Instagram API: integration with the Instagram API allows users to connect their Instagram accounts, retrieve posts, and generate comments.
- Comment Customization: Users have the ability to edit the generated comments

The platform's backend is built using Flask and deployed on Oracle Cloud.
projects.title: AI platform for automatic generation of social media comments

projects.description: The Telegram Chatbot for Detecting Hateful and Offensive Messages is a machine learning project that utilizes NLP to detect inappropriate messages in Telegram chat groups. Developed using TypeScript and the grammY framework, the chatbot assigns a score to messages based on the likelihood of being offensive and sends a notification to administrators if the score exceeds a certain threshold. Customizable and trainable, the chatbot is designed to improve its accuracy over time, ensuring a safer and more inclusive environment for Telegram chat groups
projects.title: ToxicBot: Telegram Bot that detects hate speech in chats using NLP
